title: 2014 UP PARLIAMENT ELECTIONS
desc:
Party wise seats
nopartySeatscolor
1BJP71
2SP5
3IND2
4INC2
The 2014 Indian general election polls in Uttar Pradesh for 80 Lok Sabha seats was held in six phases on 10, 17, 24, 30 April and 7, 12 May 2014.The total voter strength of Uttar Pradesh was 134,351,297.The main political parties in Uttar Pradesh are Bahujan Samaj Party (BSP), Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP), Indian National Congress (INC) and Samajwadi party (SP). BJP allied with Apna Dal and INC allied with Rashtriya Lok Dal and Mahan Dal
